    "c, Social identity biases in LLMs tested with the instruction prompt (N = 76,000 sentences).",
    "d, Social identity biases in human data obtained from four different pretraining corpora (N = 16,000 sentences).",
    "https://doi.org/10.1038/s43588-024-00741-1",
    "Our findings for instruction fine-tuned models prompted with the instruction prompt indicate that they exhibited lower ingroup solidarity and outgroup hostility compared to the base LLMs (Fig. 1c).",
    "This was evidenced by lower odds ratios, which mostly remain below 2, and several models demonstrating statistically non-significant ingroup solidarity or outgroup hostility (Supplementary Table 12)."
